GIt - notes

Config GIT to the machine
    • git config --global user.name "<<User Name>>"
    • git config --global user.email "<<Email address>>"

Create a folder and initiliase the GIT.
    • git init

Git Staging Environment. “git add <<file names>>” 
    • To add all the files we need to append “--all” at the end.
    • Multiple files can be added with comma seperated files names.
    • Specifing the file name will allow us to add specific file to the staging env.
Staging env is the something will help to track the updated of the file.

Git status:
    • It will provide the changes that are ready to commit.

Git commit:
    • Git commit -m “<<Commit message>>” - will do the commit.
    • Git commit -a  “<<Commit message>>” - “-a” will allow to commit changes directly. -> provide the comment and the ctrl+X

Git commit log:
    • will provide the log history.

Git help : git <<command>> -help, git help –all [provide entire help content].

Git branch :
    • Create New branch : git branch <<branch name>> : git branch naveen
    • 



